---
// Beverage-Air Repair Los Angeles — HUB
// /brands/beverage-air/
// Cluster 02 Commercial Refrigeration · Hub + combo (cross-cluster 4 services: 2+14+15+16)
// Widest cross-cluster brand in all of commercial. Ali Group family bridge page.
// Wraps existing combo at /brands/commercial-refrigeration/beverage-air-commercial-repair/
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Beverage-Air Repair Los Angeles | Same Day Service";
const description = "Same-day Beverage-Air SP prep, HR back bar, UCR undercounter, DR display, MT reach-in repair in LA. Ali Group family. $120 diag. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/beverage-air/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Beverage-Air part of Ali Group or still independent?",
    a: "Ali Group. Beverage-Air has been under Ali North America since 1991, originally as part of the Specialty Equipment Companies acquisition and now as a direct Ali brand headquartered in Winston-Salem, North Carolina. The 2022 Welbilt acquisition by Ali North America ($3.5 billion) expanded the Ali family dramatically: post-2022, Beverage-Air sits alongside Delfield, Manitowoc, Kolpak, Master-Bilt, Nor-Lake, Lincoln, Garland, Pitco, Frymaster, Convotherm, and Merrychef under the same parent. That's the practical reason an LA restaurant running a mixed Ali fleet (Beverage-Air reach-in + Kolpak walk-in + Manitowoc ice + Champion dishwasher) now has a single parts supply channel. SERP content older than 2022 still describes Beverage-Air as part of a different corporate tree — most of it's out of date."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Beverage-Air SP, HR, and UCR lines?",
    a: "Three different positions on the LA kitchen or bar line. SP (and the SPE / SPED variants) is the sandwich and salad prep table — the refrigerated base with the cold-rail lid at the make-line, same functional category as True's TSSU. HR is the horizontal back-bar refrigerator, the under-bar bottle cooler you see running behind an LA bar or cocktail lounge — doors open every 30 seconds during Friday service, highest door-cycle count in the BA catalog. UCR is the undercounter reach-in, sized for prep kitchens where vertical space is tight and refrigeration at the worktop matters more than walk-up storage. Our techs see failure modes cluster by product line: SP gasket wear on the rail lid, HR condenser clogs in the bar cabinet environment, UCR door hinge failure from repeated bend-down-and-open motion."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Beverage-Air bar equipment on Friday/weekend emergency?",
    a: "Yes — and we prioritize Friday through Sunday bar calls because the failure dynamics are punishing. A Beverage-Air HR back-bar cooler at a Silver Lake cocktail bar or a DTLA rooftop goes down on Saturday night, and the operator loses the weekend. Our after-hours dispatch covers the West Hollywood bar corridor, Silver Lake and Echo Park neighborhood bars, DTLA cocktail rooms, Arts District craft-cocktail operators, Santa Monica and Hollywood nightlife. Commercial diagnostic $120 waived with repair; after-hours premium $180 is quoted before we dispatch so there's no surprise at invoice. Most Friday-night BA calls we run are gasket blowouts or compressor thermal trips from a dirty condenser — both fixable same-visit if we have the call by early evening."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you service Beverage-Air HR back-bar units under active warranty?",
    a: "Depends on the warranty status and the failure mode. Beverage-Air ships new units with a standard 1-year parts and labor warranty plus 5-year compressor warranty through the authorized Beverage-Air service network. If your unit is inside the 1-year window and needs warranty work, that has to go through the authorized channel — we tell you that upfront rather than taking the call and creating a paperwork problem. If the unit is out of warranty, or the specific repair isn't covered (maintenance items, user-damage items, cosmetic components), we handle it as a standard paid repair. For the 5-year compressor specifically, call the Beverage-Air service locator first — the compressor warranty has to be processed through authorized parts supply. We'll still handle the diagnostic if you want a second-opinion quote."
  },
  {
    q: "How often should Beverage-Air bar undercounters be condenser-cleaned in an LA bar?",
    a: "Quarterly. Every three months minimum. Bar undercounter coolers are the worst condenser-clog environment we service in LA — the condenser sits in a cabinet with minimal airflow, ambient temp rises during service, alcohol residue mixes with LA dust, and the fin spacing packs tight. We see HR and UCR units fail on compressor thermal overload trip at 18-24 months in a bar that never cleaned its condenser; the same unit in a bar on a quarterly maintenance contract holds temperature reliably past 10 years. The economics are straightforward: a $200 quarterly condenser cleaning beats a $1,800 compressor replacement every 2-3 years. Our preventive maintenance contract includes coil cleaning, door gasket check, refrigerant pressure verification, and thermostat calibration — billed per visit or annually."
  },
  {
    q: "Is Beverage-Air worth repairing at 10-12 years old?",
    a: "Usually yes. Beverage-Air is mid-market positioning — not the premium tier of True or Traulsen, not the budget tier of Atosa or Avantco — and the build quality is sized for 12 to 15 years of commercial service with normal maintenance. Our field rule: on a BA unit 10-12 years old with a sub-$1,500 repair quote, fix it. Over $2,500 on a 12-plus-year-old unit with a failing compressor, we run the replacement math. Beverage-Air's current-production pricing is moderate — a replacement HR back-bar or SP prep table is usually $3,500-$6,500 installed — so the repair-to-replace threshold hits faster than it does on premium brands. We'll quote both sides honestly when the call is close."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Beverage-Air repair typically cost in LA?",
    a: "Commercial diagnostic is $120, waived with authorized repair. Typical repair bands we invoice: door gasket $180-$360 installed; HR back-bar door hinge cartridge $240-$480; evaporator fan motor $320-$580; thermostat or electronic controller $220-$440; condenser coil deep cleaning $200-$360; TXV replacement $400-$780; refrigerant recharge $380-$820; compressor replacement $1,600-$3,400 on standard reach-ins (higher on larger MT or custom condensing packages). Full cost ranges by repair type are in our <a href=\"/price-list/commercial-refrigerator-repair-cost/\">commercial refrigerator repair pricing</a> guide. We quote the full job before starting, separate labor / parts / refrigerant as three line items, and apply the $120 diagnostic credit to the repair total."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — Beverage-Air Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/logo.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": "+1-424-325-0520",
    "priceRange": "$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "Beverage-Air Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Beverage-Air commercial refrigeration repair across Los Angeles — SP / SPE prep tables, HR back-bar coolers, UCR undercounter, DR glass-door merchandisers, MT mega-top reach-ins, freezer variants. Ali Group family, Winston-Salem NC. EPA 608 certified, same-day dispatch.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "120.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Commercial diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a.replace(/<[^>]+>/g, '') }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Beverage-Air", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <style>
    :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, sans-serif; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.6; }
    a { color: inherit; }
    .call-banner { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 10px 20px; text-align: center; font-size: 14px; }
    .call-banner a.phone-lg { color: #fff; text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 700; margin-left: 8px; }
    .wrap { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
    .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
    .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 64px 0 56px; }
    .hero .crumb { font-size: 12px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); margin-bottom: 14px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
    .hero .crumb a { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5); text-decoration: none; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(30px, 4.5vw, 44px); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0 0 18px; }
    .hero .lede { font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.65; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75); max-width: 720px; margin: 0 0 26px; }
    .hero-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 40px; align-items: start; }
    @media (max-width: 860px) { .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
    .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 13px 24px; border-radius: 6px; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; font-size: 15px; }
    .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; }
    .btn-ghost { background: transparent; border: 1.5px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3); color: #fff; }
    .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .hero-facts li { font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72); padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); }
    .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: none; }
    .hero-facts b { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }
    .hero-aside .aside-card { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12); border-radius: 12px; padding: 22px 20px; }
    .aside-card h3 { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55); margin: 0 0 14px; }
    .branch { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08); color: #fff; font-size: 14px; text-decoration: none; }
    .branch:first-of-type { border-top: none; }
    .branch b { font-weight: 600; }
    .branch span { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55); font-size: 13px; }
    .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 12px 24px; }
    .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; }
    .section { padding: 60px 0; }
    .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
    .section h2 { font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 30px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 0 0 18px; }
    .section p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; margin: 0 0 16px; }
    .section p.intro { font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 28px; max-width: 720px; }
    .model-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 28px; }
    .model-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 22px 20px; }
    .section.alt .model-card { background: #fff; }
    .model-card h3 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; }
    .model-card p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.65; }
    .fact-block { background: #fff; border-left: 4px solid var(--red); padding: 22px 24px; margin-top: 28px; }
    .section.alt .fact-block { background: #fff; border-left-color: var(--red); }
    .fact-block h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 10px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--red); }
    .fact-block p { font-size: 15px; margin: 0 0 12px; line-height: 1.7; }
    .fact-block p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .area-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(240px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 24px; }
    .area-grid div h4 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; margin: 0 0 6px; color: var(--text); }
    .area-grid div p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--muted); margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }
    .area-grid div a { color: var(--red); text-decoration: underline; }
    .faq { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 18px 0; }
    .faq:first-of-type { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .faq summary { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; list-style: none; padding-right: 24px; position: relative; }
    .faq summary::after { content: "+"; position: absolute; right: 0; top: 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 400; color: var(--red); }
    .faq[open] summary::after { content: "−"; }
    .faq p { font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.75; margin: 12px 0 0; }
    .faq p :global(a) { color: var(--red); text-decoration: underline; }
    .related-links { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 20px 0 0; }
    .related-links li { padding: 10px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 15px; }
    .related-links li:first-child { border-top: none; }
    .related-links a { color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
    .related-links a:hover { color: var(--red); }
    .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 60px 0; text-align: center; }
    .bottom-cta h2 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .bottom-cta p { color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65); max-width: 540px; margin: 0 auto 26px; }
    .bottom-cta .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  </style>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <span>Beverage-Air unit down? Call now for same-day service:</span>
    <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="phone-lg">(424) 325-0520</a>
  </div>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Beverage-Air</div>
          <h1>Beverage-Air Repair Los Angeles</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            Beverage-Air is the widest cross-cluster commercial refrigeration brand our techs service in LA — reach-ins,
            back-bar coolers, undercounter, display cases, prep tables, and freezers all ship under the same roof. Ali
            Group family since 1991, Winston-Salem North Carolina headquarters, and the anchor brand for the post-2022
            Ali roster that now spans Delfield, Manitowoc, Kolpak, Master-Bilt, Nor-Lake, Lincoln, Garland, Pitco,
            Frymaster, Convotherm, and Merrychef. Same-day dispatch across LA and the five SoCal counties. $120
            commercial diagnostic waived with the repair, EPA 608 certified team.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="btn btn-primary">Call (424) 325-0520</a>
            <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>Full Beverage-Air family coverage</b> — SP, HR, UCR, DR, MT, CF, and freezer variants</li>
            <li><b>$120 commercial diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
            <li><b>5 branches</b>: West Hollywood · Los Angeles · Thousand Oaks · Pasadena · Irvine</li>
            <li><b>Ali Group parts network</b> — single-vendor supply with Kolpak, Master-Bilt, Champion, Manitowoc</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <aside class="hero-aside">
          <div class="aside-card">
            <h3>Talk to a local branch</h3>
            <a href="tel:+13238704790" class="branch"><b>West Hollywood</b><span>(323) 870-4790</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="branch"><b>Los Angeles</b><span>(424) 325-0520</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+14242080228" class="branch"><b>Thousand Oaks</b><span>(424) 208-0228</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+16263764458" class="branch"><b>Pasadena</b><span>(626) 376-4458</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+12134019019" class="branch"><b>Irvine</b><span>(213) 401-9019</span></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>★ 4.6 / 37 Google reviews</span>
      <span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Commercial diagnostic $120 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- H2 #1 — POSITIONING -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>Beverage-Air — the full Ali Group commercial refrigeration line</h2>
      <p>
        Beverage-Air was founded in 1944 in New Jersey, moved through Specialty Equipment Companies in the late 1980s,
        and landed under Ali Group in 1991. Today the headquarters sits in Winston-Salem, North Carolina, and
        Beverage-Air anchors the Ali North America commercial refrigeration roster — it's the cross-cluster brand, the
        one that shows up in reach-in, back-bar, undercounter, display, and prep-table form-factors in the same LA
        restaurant. When an LA operator asks us for a single brand that can cover four or five equipment slots in the
        kitchen and bar, Beverage-Air is the answer about 60% of the time.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's mid-market positioning, not premium. True and Traulsen sit at the top of the commercial refrigeration
        market with pricing that reflects it; Beverage-Air targets the middle — price-competitive for a restaurant
        building out a new kitchen, reliable enough for 12-plus years of service with normal maintenance, serviceable
        through the Ali parts network. The operators who chose Beverage-Air for their original fit-out typically
        chose it for the same reason our techs service it: it's straightforward equipment that holds up to a real
        LA kitchen workload.
      </p>
      <p>
        Model-by-model repair detail, error codes, and specific failure walkthroughs live on the
        <a href="/brands/commercial-refrigeration/beverage-air-commercial-repair/">Beverage-Air commercial refrigeration combo page</a>.
        This hub covers the positioning, the Ali family context, the LA customer segments, and the seven
        most-asked-about questions our techs get on Beverage-Air calls.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- H2 #2 — WHAT WE FIX -->
  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>What our techs fix across the Beverage-Air family</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Six product families, six distinct failure patterns. Pattern recognition from running Beverage-Air calls across
        LA commercial kitchens and bars every week.
      </p>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Reach-ins — MT, KR, KF upright configurations</h3>
        <p>
          Door gasket first (frost ring at the jamb, fog rolling out harder than it used to), evaporator fan motor
          second (bearing noise that telegraphed the failure for weeks), compressor thermal overload trip third
          (almost always traced back to a condenser coil packed with LA kitchen dust and grease). We carry gaskets
          and common fan motor sizes on the truck. The MT mega-top reach-in runs a slightly different condensing
          package and is our more common "call back in 6-9 months" unit because the rooftop-style condenser fouls
          faster in grease-heavy Koreatown and Valley environments.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Back-bar coolers — HR and BM bottle coolers</h3>
        <p>
          Our highest-door-cycle commercial refrigeration product. At an LA bar running Friday and Saturday service,
          an HR back-bar door opens hundreds of times across a shift. Hinge cartridge wear in 18-24 months at that
          cadence, gasket compression loss at 12-18 months, door heater failure on freezer-variant units, condenser
          clogs accelerated by alcohol-residue airflow. We see these fail during Friday service and we dispatch them
          at top-priority commercial rate because the inventory and revenue loss compound by the hour.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Undercounter — UCR and UCF worktop and drawer units</h3>
        <p>
          Lives under the prep counter or at the make-line. Failure pattern skews toward mechanical — door hinge
          failure from the repeated bend-down-and-open motion, drawer slide wear on drawer-configured units, and
          gasket damage from closing into a prep bowl or a meat pan. Refrigeration-side failures are less frequent
          than on HR back-bars because the environment is cleaner, but when the compressor goes the replacement
          cost matters because the unit is often difficult to pull from under a built-in counter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Display cases and glass-door merchandisers — DR and MM series</h3>
        <p>
          LED driver failure is the signature call on glass-door units — the driver sits in the top frame, runs
          continuously, fails quietly. Gasket replacement and hinge work follow. At LA convenience stores, delis,
          and specialty groceries, DR display cases also see accelerated condenser wear from exposed-retail ambient
          conditions (dust infiltration, customer proximity, extended door-open windows).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Sandwich and prep tables — SP, SPE, SPED lines</h3>
        <p>
          Same functional category as True's TSSU. The make-line cold rail fails first (small evaporator, sensitive
          to airflow blockage from pan placement), base-door gasket second, refrigerant drift third on units over
          eight years old. Our techs carry rail-specific parts for Beverage-Air's SPE and SPED generations because
          the call rate on prep tables at LA delis, sushi counters, and taqueria lines is the highest of any
          Beverage-Air product family.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fact-block">
        <h3>Freezer variants — the -F-suffix catalog</h3>
        <p>
          Beverage-Air runs freezer variants across most of its reach-in, back-bar, and undercounter lines (model
          suffix "F" or dedicated freezer series designation). Freezer failure dynamics differ from cooler: door
          heater wear to prevent jamb-ice, defrost cycle failures, and compressor thermal trips from the harder
          workload. We cover these under the same commercial diagnostic structure as the refrigerator side.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- H2 #3 — PRODUCT FAMILY MAP -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>Product family map — SP, HR, UCR, DR, MT, CF, and freezer variants</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Where each Beverage-Air product line sits in the LA kitchen or bar layout. The
        <a href="/brands/commercial-refrigeration/beverage-air-commercial-repair/">commercial combo page</a>
        goes deeper on model-specific repair workflows; this is the map.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>SP / SPE / SPED — sandwich & salad prep</h3>
          <p>Make-line refrigerated base with cold-rail lid. LA deli, sushi bar, taqueria, counter-service prep.
          Highest dispatch rate per unit across the Beverage-Air catalog.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>HR / BM — horizontal back-bar coolers</h3>
          <p>Under-bar bottle coolers and draft-beer adjunct units. Runs behind LA bars and cocktail lounges.
          Highest door-cycle count in the BA catalog.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>UCR / UCF — undercounter reach-ins</h3>
          <p>Undercounter worktop and drawer configurations. Lives under the prep counter where vertical space is
          tight. Mechanical failure modes dominate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>DR / MM — display & merchandiser</h3>
          <p>Glass-door merchandisers for delis, convenience stores, specialty groceries. LED driver + hinge +
          gasket are the top three call types.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>MT / KR / KF — upright reach-ins</h3>
          <p>Walk-up reach-in refrigerators and freezers sized 1, 2, and 3 doors. MT mega-top variant runs a
          rooftop-style condensing package that needs closer attention in grease environments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>CF — chef base / equipment stand</h3>
          <p>Refrigerated equipment stand for cooking-line integration. Sits under a griddle, char-broiler, or
